  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Austrian Twin </strong>rooms have a bath. Some of these rooms have balconies and can sleep two adults and one child up to 13 years using a pull-out bed.</p>
<p><strong>Family Room Superiors </strong>can sleep three to four - one room with Austrian twins beds and separate room with lounge area with a double sofa bed and a put up bed. These rooms have a bath and a balcony.</p>
<p><strong>Twin Room Superiors </strong>can sleep two guests and have a bath, lounge area and balcony.</p>
<p><strong>Single Superior </strong>rooms have a shower and a balcony.</p>
<p><span>The main hotel building is the original building, which houses the reception, dining room and some guest bedrooms. Two newer wings are connected to the main building, one is decorated in a traditional Tyrolean style and the other has a more modern style. Location of newer wing rooms can be requested at the time of booking but not guaranteed.</span></p>
<p><strong>Bedroom Facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Cable / satellite TV</li>
<li>Minibar / fridge</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Kettle (Tea and coffee not supplied but guests can purchase themselves or purchase from reception)</li>
<li>Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
